        "created_at": "2026-01-07T22:31:42.186Z",
        "cooked": "<p>others probably put more moderate answers, although still similar. this is something that i\u2019m opinionated mouthpiece.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"givens\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74085\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/85f322/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> givens:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I am someone who generally enjoys privacy, but I am not in a situation where my liberty or safety is at stake.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>-</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"givens\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74085\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/85f322/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> givens:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I find Apple privacy sometimes opaque and misleading.  They market their devices using privacy as a differentiator but their privacy policy describes how they share much data with partners that I find to be personal. I have not determined how to prevent sharing or lock down my privacy for Apple apps and perhaps others</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>apple collects data like other big tech companies. apple may not show ads but still collects data for whatever purposes.</p>\n<p>apple gives pretty much zero control for its users. because of that, apple is worse than other companies like google. google might be data collection nightmare, but at least android is still cleanable, although difficult task.</p>\n<p>as of now, i think future of android is doomed into walled garden.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"givens\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74085\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/85f322/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> givens:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I remain concerned about E2EE on the iOS Signal app. My specific concern is that the input generally uses the Apple keyboard, and the keyboard is predictive. This suggests it is aware of what I am typing prior to it being E2EE on the Signal app.  Potentially every keystroke is exposed</p>\n<p>I have a sense these operations happen on device, but I do not know what Apple stores or sends to servers.  Is anyone aware of privacy limitations of this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>signal org cannot secure underlying operating system. ultimately no one can guarantee what is going on in apple devices.</p>\n<p>i don\u2019t personally believe that apple has a keylogger in operating system or keyboard app. personally, i don\u2019t trust apple anymore either.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"givens\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74085\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/85f322/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> givens:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I would love to understand Apple privacy better  it may be deliberately opaque.</p>\n<p>I did a cursory search on this forum  for related topics and did not find anything that explained Apple keyboard privacy limitations in regard to the Signal app. I hope I did not overlook the answer.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>",
